==============================================================================
Manuscript-ready sentence (paste into Sample Characteristics):
==============================================================================
Healthy controls (N = 2,004 for depression and obesity; N = 2,004 for hypertension) differed from incident depression cases (N = 463) on annual household income (>100k: HC 52.8%, incident 38.2%; V = 0.13); differed from incident obesity cases (N = 457) on sex (Female: HC 65.2%, incident 52.1%; V = 0.10) and annual household income (>100k: HC 52.8%, incident 42.0%; V = 0.11); and differed from incident hypertension cases (N = 270) on sex (Female: HC 65.2%, incident 34.4%; V = 0.20) and race/ethnicity (White: HC 67.0%, incident 54.8%; V = 0.12) and annual household income (>100k: HC 52.8%, incident 37.8%; V = 0.12).